 Cannavaro, Emerson set for Real

Madrid: Italys World Cup-winning captain Fabio Cannavaro and Brazilian midfielder Emerson have agreed to join Real Madrid from troubled Serie A side Juventus, the Primera Liga club said on Wednesday. 

Real Madrid would like to announce theyve reached an agreement with Juventus for the signing of Fabio Cannavaro and Emerson, the Spanish club said on its website on Wednesday. 

Real did not disclose the cost of the deal but Spanish media said they would pay about 20 million euros ($24.99 million) for the pair who will be reunited with ex-Juve coach Fabio Capello who took charge of the nine-time European champions this month. 

Meanwhile, European champions Barcelona are set to sign Juventus defenders Lilian Thuram and Gianluca Zambrotta, according to Spanish newspaper reports. 

Barcelona sporting director Aitor Begiristain said he hoped to be able to announce the signings before Monday, with one daily claiming Zambrotta will cost 14 million euros and Thuram five million euros. 

Zambrotta is expected to sign a four-year contract, while Thurams personal terms will be agreed upon he returns from a holiday in South Africa. (Agencies) 




